<dl id="n17036d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n17" href="#n17036d">N17 (VI.B.9)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n17all.htm#n17036d"> 36(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> peau de / chagrin / Shagreen <small>Orange</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n17036d"><li>FW 186.08 </li><li><a href="../../flex/g/lexg.htm#n17036d">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/g/l39g.htm#n17036d">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n17036d">MS BL 47474-65</ms> </li><li>JJA 47:443 <a name="gd4" href="../../FF/fdra/gda.htm#gd4">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/g/gd4.htm#n17036d">Draft: I.7&sect;1.4</a>/2.4</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Je fus distraite par un homme vis-&agrave;-vis de ma loge. Il semblait voir les autres, et prendre du plaisir avec <mark>un peu de chagrin</mark>: je demandai quel &eacute;tait cet animal taciturne. &ldquo;Tais-toi, me dit Ariste, respecte davantage cet homme, c&apos;est un Suisse civilis&eacute; dans les montagnes de Savoie par un tonsur&eacute;: il se f&acirc;che contre toi, &agrave; cause que tu sens du plaisir &agrave; l&apos;Op&eacute;ra; il assure que tout ce qui t&apos;enchante ne doit pas plus affecter l&apos;&acirc;me d&apos;un homme de go&ucirc;t que ton mouchoir de poche au bout de ma canne. <font color="green">[I was distracted by a man opposite my box. He seemed to see the others, and to take pleasure with a little heartache: I asked who this taciturn animal was. "Shut up," said Ariste, "respect this man more, he is a Swiss citizen, civilized in the mountains of Savoy by a tonsure; he is angry with you because you feel pleasure at the Opera; he assures me that everything that enchants you should not affect the soul of a man of taste more than your pocket-handkerchief at the end of my cane.]</font> <small> Henri-Joseph Dulaurens, <a name="IMIR" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#IMIR"><cite title="source">Imirce ou la fille de la nature</cite></a> (1765, new ed. 1922) (?) 112</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Fr. <i>Peau de chagrin</i>, rough skin. See also <a name="n09071c" href="n09all.htm#n09071c">N09 (VI.B.1):071(c)</a>. Balzac&apos;s <cite>Le Peau de chargin</cite>, The Ass&apos;s Skin, model for Oscar Wilde&apos;s <cite>The Picture of Dorian Gray</cite> (see also <a name="n17036e" href="n17all.htm#n17036e">N17 (VI.B.9):036(e)</a> below). </mm> </dd></dl>
